# CODEOWNERS — defense-in-depth for the self-hosting Dev-mesh.
#
# The mesh's do-workers push with DEV_MESH_PAT (a PAT with `workflows` scope) so the
# Coder can land fixes that touch workflow files — the Actions GITHUB_TOKEN is barred
# from .github/workflows/** by GitHub. That means the mesh can now AUTHOR changes to its
# own CI / safety harness on a branch. This file makes the human merge gate explicit and
# specific for those changes: any PR touching a workflow file (or this file) requires
# review from the repo owner.
#
# NOTE: CODEOWNERS is only *enforced* when branch protection on `main` has
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled. Set that on, or this is advisory only.

/.github/workflows/   @danabaxia
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @danabaxia
